items.name: Elbia Hanaiman (Outbreak Company)
items.description:
This is a lycors\locon you have to use the additional networks extension or the lycoris extension for this to work.

I made a twitter account which you can find in the little box where my username and all that datastuff is located. I will upload previews pictures for model im currently working on there or stuff that that I can't post here and information about the new model im working on.

You should read some of the description. This model might be difficult to use.

Let's skip the introduction and just get to the details because this model is difficult to use in my opinion.

First of I would recommend using a style model because most of the data were from the artist who drew the pictures for the light novel so it kind of defaults to that style which has a bit washed out colors but looks alright overall. I used cfg scale 7 for all my gens but maybe adjusting that might help with the colors.

Keyword is Elbia Hanaiman. I pruned her ear and tail and her skin/eye and hair color but i would recommend prompting those as well to get them consistently, or at least her animal features and maybe her skin color if you don't prompt her skin color she will be a bit paler but not "whitewashed" but that might also depend on your checkpoint.

If you want her default outfit use tags like: bandeau, pants (you might have to add the color) armlet, necklace and bare shoulders

I will include some images that i made during testing which are from an older model but the old model was inferior in most aspects.

This model is not perfect and I might retrain it one or two more times with other settings.

Things that might happen include: double animal ears, wrong color of her top (might be because of the pants), weird tail but that might also depend on your checkpoint, missing ears, wrong hair color if you want to gen nudes you might have to add more weight to the tag you are using to disable her clothing.

Thats the one i found so far.

So with everything out of the way let's talk about the character.

Most of you might not know her she is a supporting character from an Anime called "Outbreak Company" but even though she has a minor role she gets her own arc which fleshes out her character pretty well.

She is energetic and very likable a top tier waifu in my opinion.

The Anime also has some banger OST if you are a fan of that genre you should totally listen to that.

Sorry for that wall of text and thank you to the people who actually read and enjoy my ramblings. Now for some copy pasta.

If you like the model consider liking, rating and commenting that would be appreciated.

Have fun generating.

items.name: Women's BOTanical Wrap Outfit - AIvante-Garde
items.description:
Add a touch of the tropics to your summer wardrobe with this Botanical Wrap Outfit consisting of a Neck Halter Tiny Top with matching Mini Skirt by AIvante-Garde™.

--

This is my first run at a clothing LoRA. It is based on a outfit I saw at every yoga mom's favorite store.

I ran training multiple times and it's a little stiff, but it produces great results with a little work. It works well with photorealistic and animated styles. It has some poses it likes to default to, but will take prompting pretty decently. I tested out some controlnet poses as well, which can be seen in the sample pictures.

Usage: Trained with "b0t4n1c4lwr4p" but it doesn't need it at all. Though, "halter top" and "skirt" help, otherwise it starts to turn into a bikini - which some may prefer. Hires fix with high Denoising ends up producing body horror, so stick low if you're using it.

I hope you like it!

items.name: ICBIN64 - I Can't Believe It's Not 64
items.description:
Making models is fairly cheap, actually. Do you like what I do? Consider becoming a GPU provider for the Stable Horde👹, donating to Ukraine 🇺🇦, or feel free to hire an actual artist 🎨.

A retro 3D-style LoRA trained on ICBINP Final. Primarily generates Ocarina of Time/Majora's Mask style human characters, but also has a substantial dataset of landscapes from various games.

Trained at Clip Skip 2. min_snr_gamma=5 and scale_weight_norms=1.0 allow for a much longer than typical training process without harsh overfitting.

items.name: Belle Delphine (Face & Body LoRA)
items.description:
Join my new Discord here! https://discord.gg/cnVvnkgtPb

Belle Delphine (Face & Body LoRA) - the infamous e-girl. This LoRA includes Belle Delphine's face AND body. Use the trigger words to get the desired result. Infinite Belle pics await you.

NSFW Previews: https://jpg.pet/aihotgirls

Read Me!

TWO VERSIONS:

  • Belle Delphine RHM v1: Trained on Real Hot Mix, my own mix. I use this LoRA for extremely high quality photorealistic results

    • For txt2img & img2img: LoRA weight between 0.9-1 for best results

  • Belle Delphine SD1.5 v1: Trained on SD 1.5 base model, compatible with all models

    • For txt2img & img2img: LoRA weight between 0.5-1 depending on checkpoint model for best results (lower for anime/non-photorealistic models)

Recommended Settings

  • Hires fix: 0.2-0.3 for face, 0.2-0.4 for full body

  • Face is best at 1:1 resolution (make sure inpainting is 1:1 resolution)

    • Other resolutions work as well (see Training Info: resolution sizing for training dataset aspect ratio info)

  • 'makeup' is a trigger word. Put it in negative and use 'brown hair' to get Belle with no makeup

  • This LoRA is NSFW skewed. Use 'clothes' in positive and '(nude:1.5), (breasts:1.5)' in negative if you want SFW pics

  • SOMETIMES:

    • If generating on not 1:1 aspect, her face may become slightly elongated. Maybe 1 in 5 images

    • 'pink hair' occasionally makes humongous hair. Not sure why this happens. I use 'huge hair, long hair' in negative if that seems to be happening with my prompt

Training Info

  • 5 epochs, 25 repeats, 36 images

    • 21 brown hair, 10 pink hair, 5 blonde hair pics (if unspecified, brown hair will usually default)

    • 22 face, 14 full body pics

  • For resolution sizing, enable buckets = true (25 = 1 image)

    • bucket 0: resolution (384, 640), count: 25

      bucket 1: resolution (384, 704), count: 75

      bucket 2: resolution (448, 576), count: 100

      bucket 3: resolution (448, 640), count: 25

      bucket 4: resolution (448, 704), count: 100

      bucket 5: resolution (512, 576), count: 25

      bucket 6: resolution (512, 640), count: 75

      bucket 7: resolution (576, 576), count: 450

      bucket 8: resolution (640, 448), count: 25

Background

I've been experimenting with LoRA training and seem to have found a sweet spot for epic photoreal accuracy for people. I didn't realize there were already so many Belle LoRAs while making this, but wanted to share anyway. I believe this one is the BEST one on Civit.

items.name: Envy Warrior 01
items.description:
Gives your characters a warrior look (even if you don't call them a warrior in the prompt).

Note that, like its creator, this model believes in the rule of cool and has no opinion about the real-world practicality of armor on fictional characters. If you want practical, realistic armor, put words like this in the prompt (potentially weighted higher than 1):

  • armor

  • faulds

  • pauldrons

  • chestplate

  • shield

  • etc

...and maybe add "nsfw" to your negative prompt if that's not enough.

items.name: Naoetsu Private High School Uniform LoRA (Monogatari Franchise)
items.description:
Naoetsu Private High School Uniform LoRA

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

This model was trained using 29 images of characters from the series and cosplays of characters wearing the school uniform. It was trained on the NAI model so it should work with most anime based models.

Recommended weight is 0.8 - 0.9. It works with other character LoRAs if you tweak the weights a bit. I recommend to use hires fix!

Trigger word is naoetsu, but I recommend adding school uniform, skirt, puffy sleeves, to make it more consistent

Example images were generated using AOM2 hard with 50 steps, then used hires fix on 0.5 denoising strength.

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

items.name: Concept monster
items.description:
EDIT: just a friendly reminder to use the trigger word "Evang" for it to actually Function

Created in Dreambooth this model provides you the ability to create extremely detailed 2D Illustration concept Creatures. works well with fantasy art creatures, not so well with people. This is not intended to make cute portraits symmetrical faces. This is meant to create scary creatures, bazaar creatures, and aliens, an ideal for concept art etc..

The latest version has been merged with this detail enhancer LoRa, credit for the creator as they made that LoRa work really well. I have noticed on some of the other models I’ve tried to merge it with it tends to make things slightly darker and gives more streaky looks to things which can look great for certain areas of an illustration like hair, etc.

https://civitai.com/models/82098/add-more-details-detail-enhancer-tweaker-lora

See my video on how I like to utilize some of these models here

Making these models can be expensive and very time consuming. If you would consider helping out, it would be much appreciated as any little bit goes a long way

https://www.buymeacoffee.com/Theprotoart

Edit: Better results with detailed prompts but you can also get some really amazing ones with simple ones kind of have to just explore.

If your image has color, try, adding the words, black and white or monochrome or even adding the word, color or colorized in the negative prompt. I have use many prompts from Lexica.art as well as from arthub.ai that have given me some really phenomenal results.

I also show you how to create your own custom models with your own art on my YouTube channel.
